Yes, accessing a missing key directly causes a KeyError. You can use the .get() method to provide fallback values instead.

```python
def params(self):
    params = {}
    for p in self.parms:
        data = self.parms[p]
        params[p] = {"default": data.get("default_value"),
                     "actual": data.get("actual_value")}
    return params
```
